article.headline: Long Beach State 108, Manhattan 94
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Shawn Hawkins scored 25 points to lead seven Long Beach State scorers in double figures in the 49ers' 108-94 victory over Manhattan on Saturday. Kevin Houston scored 17 points and Kejuan Johnson added 16 for Long Beach State (13-11), which outscored Manhattan 32-8 in bench points. Arturo Dubois scored a career-high 27 points and added nine rebounds and three steals for Manhattan (16-9). Jeff Xavier had 21 points seven rebounds, five assists and four steals and Devon Austin added 20 points, eight rebounds and three steals, but it wasn't enough for the Jaspers. Long Beach State rattled off 10 of the last 12 points in the opening half to take a 50-43 advantage at the break. Reserve guard Louis Darby triggered a run of 10 unanswered points and put the 49ers ahead to stay with two foul shots that created a 42-41 edge with 2:47 left. Manhattan pulled within 81-79 on Mike Konovelchick's layup, but the 49ers responded with an 11-1 run that culminated in Hawkins' dunk with just under 4 minutes remaining. The Jaspers drew within 94-90 on Austin's two free throws, but never got any closer. Long Beach State sealed the victory with eight consecutive points. Six of those came off free throws by Johnson.
